Author: Jens Henrik Göbbert Index Markdown Tipps &amp; Tricks (for Jupyter Notebook) <p>This text will be italic This will also be italic</p> <p>This text will be bold This will also be bold</p> <p>You can combine them</p> <pre><code>code
*This text will be italic*  
_This will also be italic_  

**This text will be bold**  
__This will also be bold__  

_You **can** combine them_  
</code></pre> <p>This is a blockquote</p> <pre><code>code
&gt; This is a blockquote
</code></pre> <ul> <li>selected item</li> <li>unselected item</li> </ul> <pre>* [x] selected item  
* [ ] unselected item
</pre> <ul> <li>One simple way of adding an image to a Markdown cell is through the following syntax</li> <li>If you want to add a hover title to the image then you can simply add it at the end</li> </ul> <p></p> <pre>![](https://www.python.org/static/community_logos/python-logo-master-v3-TM.png "Python Logo")
</pre> <ul> <li>You can also use the reference-style format for the images:</li> </ul> <p></p> <pre>![][some-id]

[some-id]: https://www.python.org/static/community_logos/python-logo-master-v3-TM.png "Python Logo"
</pre> <ul> <li>You can also control the size of the image and its position </li> </ul> <pre>&lt;div&gt;
  &lt;img src=https://www.python.org/static/community_logos/python-logo-master-v3-TM.png title="Python Logo" width="120" style="float:left"/&gt;
  &lt;img src=https://www.python.org/static/community_logos/python-logo-master-v3-TM.png title="Python Logo" width="240" style="float:center"/&gt;
  &lt;img src=https://www.python.org/static/community_logos/python-logo-master-v3-TM.png title="Python Logo" width="360" style="float:right"/&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre> <ul> <li>Drop-in image You can attach an image (or animated gif) to the notebook and make it part of the .ipynb file. Simply drag-and-drop it to the notebook. ATTENTION The image will be stored in the notebook. If you do not reference to them any more they will automatically be removed from the notebook!</li> </ul> <p></p> <pre><code>code
![mind_blown.gif](attachment:23203f8f-980e-4dc6-a95d-fbaa16e37477.gif)
</code></pre> Tip: Use blue boxes (alert-info) for tips and notes.  <pre>&lt;div class="alert alert-block alert-info"&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Tip:&lt;/b&gt;
Use blue boxes (alert-info) for tips and notes.
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre> Example: Use yellow boxes for examples that are not inside code cells, or use for mathematical formulas if needed. Typically also used to display warning messages.  <pre>&lt;div class="alert alert-block alert-warning"&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Example:&lt;/b&gt;
Use yellow boxes for examples that are not inside code cells, or use for mathematical formulas if needed.
Typically also used to display warning messages.
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre> Success: This alert box indicates a successful or positive action.  <pre>&lt;div class="alert alert-block alert-success"&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Success:&lt;/b&gt;
This alert box indicates a successful or positive action.
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre>  "alert alert-secondary" role="alert" Danger: This alert box indicates a dangerous or potentially negative action.  <pre>&lt;div class="alert alert-block alert-danger"&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Danger:&lt;/b&gt;
This alert box indicates a dangerous or potentially negative action.
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre> <code> Useful for highlighting to grab the attention of the reader towards certain points. </code> <pre>&lt;code style="background:yellow;color:black"&gt;
Useful for highlighting to grab the attention of the reader towards certain points.
&lt;/code&gt;
</pre> <p>Do not forget to buy milk today.</p> <pre>Do not forget to buy &lt;mark&gt;milk&lt;/mark&gt; today.
</pre> <p>I also tend to use the following color style when adding a piece of terminal code to a Markdown cell:</p> <p> <code>C:\Users\YOUR_USERNAME&gt; pip3 install roughviz</code> </p> <pre>&lt;p style="background:black"&gt;
&lt;code style="background:black;color:white"&gt;C:\Users\YOUR_USERNAME&gt; pip3 install roughviz&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
</pre> <p> </p> <pre>&lt;video controls="controls"
       src="https://test-videos.co.uk/vids/bigbuckbunny/mp4/h264/720/Big_Buck_Bunny_720_10s_1MB.mp4" 
       poster="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Big.Buck.Bunny.-.Frank.Rinky.Gimera.png"
       width="640" height="360" type="video/mp4"&gt;
    &lt;img alt="HTML5 MP4/H.264 Video" 
         src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Big.Buck.Bunny.-.Frank.Rinky.Gimera.png" 
         title="No video playback capabilities" 
         width="640" height="360"&gt;
&lt;/video&gt;
</pre> <ul> <li>YouTubes Videos</li> </ul> In [4]: Copied! <pre>from IPython.display import YouTubeVideo
YouTubeVideo('1j_HxD4iLn8', height=480, width=640, start=30)
</pre> from IPython.display import YouTubeVideo YouTubeVideo('1j_HxD4iLn8', height=480, width=640, start=30) Out[4]: <ul> <li>HTPS-Webpages</li> </ul> In [5]: Copied! <pre>from IPython.display import IFrame
IFrame('https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTPS', width=800, height=450)
</pre> from IPython.display import IFrame IFrame('https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTPS', width=800, height=450) Out[5]: <ul> <li>PDFs</li> </ul> In [6]: Copied! <pre>from IPython.display import IFrame
IFrame('https://arxiv.org/pdf/1406.2661.pdf', width=800, height=450)
</pre> from IPython.display import IFrame IFrame('https://arxiv.org/pdf/1406.2661.pdf', width=800, height=450) Out[6]:
